0.1 Visualise Fit Non-linear Model

The data appear to behave like an exponential decay model. This may be useful in the absence of more data to fit a GAM, which would be the ideal situation.

ggplot(dat, aes(x = dist, y = mean_count_pot)) +
   geom_count() +
   stat_smooth(
      method = "nls",
      formula = y ~ SSasymp(x, Asym, R0, lrc),
      se = FALSE,
      colour = usq_cols("usq yellow")
   ) +
   ylab("Mean lesion count values") +
   xlab("Distance (m)") +
   theme_usq(base_size = 15)

0.2 Model

mod1 <- nls(mean_count_pot ~ SSasymp(dist, Asym, R0, lrc), data = dat)

RSS.p <- sum(residuals(mod1)^2)
TSS <- sum((dat$mean_count_pot - mean(dat$mean_count_pot))^2)
r2 <- 1 - (RSS.p/TSS)
paste("R2:", r2)

0.3 Thoughts

The diagnostic plots dont look so great for this data. Better starting values might help if we optimised the nls.

The R2 value is also roughly the same as the GAMs weve been looking at.

While this model may have some utility, maybe best to focus on GAMs for the time being.
